** Title: **

Aviation Mission Planning Training Lead

** Your KBR future – delivering solutions and changing the world **

** About KBR: **

** We are a company of innovators, thinkers, creators, explorers, volunteers and dreamers who all share one goal — to improve the world. **

KBR delivers science, technology and engineering solutions to governments and
companies around the world. KBR employs approximately 34,000 people performing
diverse, complex, and mission-critical roles in 33 countries.

For 65 years, KBR and its heritage companies are proud to have delivered some
of Australia’s largest and most complex projects.

With around 2,000 employees in 6 primary offices throughout Australia, we are
committed to social and environmental sustainability and delivering projects
with a digital mindset driving innovation within our business and for our
customers.

We help ensure mission success on land, in the air, at sea, in space and
cyberspace for our defence customers. From individual technologies and
services to comprehensive project delivery and mission execution, no other
company can match the breadth and depth of KBR.

KBR comprises a diverse team who provide a broad spectrum of capabilities
across Australia and the Asia Pacific. Our proven project teams readily
address complex and multi-disciplinary activities, providing low-risk and
cost-effective solutions to the defence force.

Learn more about our business here.

** The Opportunity: **

We are currently seeking Expression of Interests from highly motivated
Training Leads who would provide technical expertise and advice to support the
Aviation Mission Planning Team.

Under direction from the Aviation Mission Planning Capability Lead, the
position would support and enforce the Training System requirements for:

  * curriculum development and maintenance 

  * analysis of change requests for training 

  * developmental activities for changes to training 

  * system reviews for training development. 

The Training Lead would be accountable to the Aviation Mission Planning
Capability Lead to provide training support for the AMS deliverables,
supported as follows:

Identify curriculum documentation and materials required to be developed,
including (but not limited to):

  * computer based training packages 

  * presentations 

  * videos, if required. 

  * Support the customer to maintain the training materials to ensure that complete and current versions of the training materials are available to meet the subsequent releases of AMS. 

  * Analyse any request for changes to training to determine whether the proposed change is correctly scoped against the agreed requirements prior to committing to the full developmental processes. 

Support to the following mandated system reviews for training development, in
accordance with the approved Training System Plan including:

  * training needs analysis review 

  * training design review 

  * pre-pilot course review 

  * training change completion audit. 

All candidates will be required to hold and maintain an active NV1 clearance.
Only candidates holding an NV1 clearance or above should apply.

